				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I don't know exactly what you mean by "bubbly", but I know that writes to $4003/$4007 cause the sequencer (that unit outputting the duty cycle in square channels) to reset, which sound like a phase reset. To avoid this, one should write to these registers only when needed, in other words when changes to the 3 high bits of the period register is desired.
<br />
<br />Hope that helps <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

